	Zorro for theatre    
	 London, July 13 (PTI): Spanish actor Antonio Banderas is all set to return to the stage for a musical adaptation of the classic film Zorba the Greek.      
	The Mask of Zorro star will play the lead role in the stage adaptation of the 1964 film based on a book by Nikos Kazantzakis. I want to go back to theatre because it is my main source, Im more a theatre actor than a film actor, Banderas said.     
	Sandra nut    
	 London (PTI): Actress Sandra Bullock believes that she is a difficult person to live with. The actress says she is lucky to have her husband Jesse James because he accepts for who she is . The star, who is stepmother to Jamess 3 kids, said: Thankfully, I married someone who loves me just the way I am and all the nuttiness that goes into to me.    
	Sun cover    
	 Paris (Reuters): Sun-seekers whose holidays are spoiled by bad weather could be reimbursed after French travel agencies launched insurance cover for unwanted interruptions to the sunshine. It will allow holiday-makers to claim back part of the cost of their trip if they suffer at least four days of rain in any one week.                                                                                                                                                                             
